<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A fascinating new series of maps and a mesmerising animation reveal Sydney's eye-popping transformation over 250 years from a swathe of virgin land to a vibrant city with a population of over five million.</p>

<p>The illustrations were commissioned by Budget Direct Travel Insurance and created using maps from the National Library of Australia and other historical sources. The series begins with illustrations based on 18th-century drawings from a Captain James Cook expedition and by a deported coat thief from London and goes on, using modern topographical surveys, to show today's thriving, picture-postcard metropolis.</p>

<p>Scroll down for a time-travel tour…</p>

